# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTION 1 — Default (Claude Code session auth)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# If you've run `claude` locally and logged in, nothing is required — the SDK
# reuses your Claude Code auth and bills against your subscription.
# Optionally set a direct Anthropic API key to bill against a separate account:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTION 2 — AWS Bedrock (bill against AWS credits)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Uncomment and fill in to route all model calls through Bedrock.
# Setting CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK=1 automatically disables Claude Code session
# auth — spending goes to AWS, not your subscription.
#
# CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK=1
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
#
# Standard AWS credential chain is honored. Pick ONE:
#   a) IAM user / access key pair
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=...
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=...     # optional — for temp credentials / SSO
#   b) Named profile (from ~/.aws/credentials)
# AWS_PROFILE=my-profile
#
# Override the model ID with your Bedrock inference-profile ID.
# Look this up in the AWS Bedrock console → Model catalog → Claude Opus → Cross-region inference.
# Example (verify the exact string in your console):
# CLAUDE_MODEL=us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-7
